quran[13]{c,v,t}:
  21,45,"Say, \"Surely I am only warning you by the Revelation.\" And (yet) they that are deaf do not hear the call (even) when they are warned"
  21,46,"And indeed in case a gust of your Lord's torment touched them, indeed they would definitely say, \"O, woe to us! Surely we were an unjust (people)"
  21,47,"And We will lay down the equitable scales for the Day of the Resurrection, so that not one self will be done an injustice in anything, and even in case it be the weight of one grain of mustard-seed, We will come up with it. And Sufficient are We for reckoners"
  21,48,"And indeed We already brought Musa and Harun (Moses and Aaron, respectively) the Furqan (The all-distinctive Criterion) and an Illumination and a Remembrance for the pious"
  21,49,"The ones who are apprehensive of their Lord in the Unseen, and they are timorous (because of) the Hour"
  21,50,And this is a blessed Remembrance that We have sent down. So are you (now) denying it
  21,51,And indeed We already brought Ibrahim (Abrahem) earlier his right-mindedness and We were Knowledgeable of him
  21,52,"As he said to his father and his people, \"What are these statues to which you are consecrating (yourselves)"
  21,53,"They said, \"We found our fathers worshiping them"
  21,54,"He said, \"Indeed you were already, you and your fathers, in evident error"
  21,55,"They said, \"Have you come to us with the Truth, or are you of the ones that play"
  21,56,"He said, \"No indeed, (but) your Lord is the Lord of the heavens and the earth Who originated them, (2) and I am of the ones who testify to this"
  21,57,"And by Allah, indeed I will definitely plot against your idols after you have withdrawn, turning away"